The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         BRIEFS
                  
	Siliguri, Aug. 16: Subash Ghisinghs wife Dhanmaya died this morning after prolonged cardiac problems, but the family was not allowed passage to the hills for the last rites. Dhanmaya, 69, died in her sons flat in Siliguri where Ghisingh, too, is staying.         
	Howrah: A 45-year-old woman was crushed under a bus at the terminus near Howrah station on Saturday. The woman, still unidentified, was crossing the road. Police said they found out that the conductor was behind the wheel of the Howrah-Salt Lake private bus when the accident happened.        
	Calcutta: The detective department on Saturday arrested six constables who had qualified for the jobs with the help of dummy candidates. The six were arrested at the Police Training School in Alipore.        
	 Siliguri: Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee, on a visit to Siliguri on Saturday, expressed concern over the Gorkha Janmukti Morchas statehood movement. He said that in no event would the state be divided, a party member said. He said he would work for an amicable solution to problems of the hill people.         
	 Barasat: A fast-track court has granted Maoist leader Himadri Sen Roy alias Somen the status of political prisoner. Any criminal case against the Maoist, arrested in February, will be lifted.                                                                                                                                                                   
